c4p.brief: GDG Cloud Auburn announcing DevFest for very first time. Be part of #war_eagle community.
c4p.content:
GDG Cloud Auburn is a community full with dazzling CS students from Auburn University and nearby universities. We build, talk and put in practice all techs Google has to offer for industrial and academic research projects.

We are hosting DevFest very first time for 100+ attendees with 3+ tracks and 10+ sessions for full day.
Submit a proposal

For DevFest 2019, we are having 3 tracks Web/mobile, Cloud, and AI/ML. Any kind of technical talks for our tracks , live-demos are allowed to present and we also allow the technology which is not directly part of any tech Google talks about but provides the essence of it.

**For Web/mobile:** Angular, Flutter, Dart, Android, Kotlin
**Cloud:** Any GCP Products, Cloud APIs, kubernetes
**AI/ML:** Tensorflow, ML APIs for mobile/web, Swift with Tensorflow

Technical talks and demos are ~50 minutes, including Q&A. We also give opportunity to give Lightning-talk of 10 minutes in which you can talk about the projects you work on using Google techs in production or inspiring our audience how ease to use and learn some tech.
c4p.title: We're looking for speakers

ihor_dvoretskyi.bio:
Ihor serves as a Developer Advocate with Kubernetes specialization for Cloud Native Computing Foundation - the Linux Foundation project, focused on creating and driving the adoption of a new computing paradigm that is optimized for modern distributed systems environments.

Ihor holds the role of Product Manager for Kubernetes at Kubernetes Open Source Community, co-driving Product Management Special Interest Group; and Program Manager at Mirantis - company, which is offering Kubernetes-based commercial solutions and services.

Apart from the product management activities, Ihor acts as a OpenStack Special Interest group co-lead at Kubernetes Community, working intensely on the questions and abilities, related to OpenStack and Kubernetes collaboration and integration.

Prior to Mirantis, Ihor has been responsible for the projects, tightly bound to Cloud computing area, containerized workloads and Linux systems.
